	| 	24	| 	2014	| 	2014-Zerocash: Decentralized Anonymous Payments from Bitcoin	| 	"比特币；匿名性；"	| 	比特币支付之间的假名,不能提供强大的隐私保证:付款交易都记录在一个公共分散的总账,可以推导出很多的信息。Zerocoin解决其中的一些隐私问题就是从原始交易中删除链接。然而,它仍然显示支付的目的地和数量,以及有限的功能。本文构建一个成熟的总账为基础的具有较强隐私保护的数字货币。构建匿名支付方案，对应交易隐藏支付者的源、目的地和转移数量。并证明了交易速度优于较少匿名的Zerocoin。	| 		| 	
	| 	25	| 	2014	| 	2014-Who Uses Bitcoin? An exploration of the Bitcoin community	| 	"比特币；交易特征；用户分析"	| 	本文提出了一种探索性的分析比特币的用户。虚拟货币和对等支付系统,比特币可能预示着未来的挑战国家监管和金融力量通过其分散结构和提供瞬时相对匿名交易。很少有人了解用户的比特币,然而。利用公开的比特币用户的调查数据,分析探讨了财富积累中比特币基金会的结构,和通过加密货币吸引用户。结果表明,年龄、首次使用时间、地理位置、采矿状态、政治倾向来帮助解释比特币财富、乐观和吸引力。	| 	Many cryptocurrencies have come into existence in recent years, with Bitcoin the most prominent among them. Although its short history has been volatile, the virtual currency maintains a core group of committed users. This paper presents an exploratory analysis of Bitcoin users. As a virtual currency and peer-to-peer payment system, Bitcoin may signal future challenges to state oversight and financial powers through its decentralized structure and offer of instantaneous transactions with relative anonymity. Very little is known about the users of Bitcoin, however. Utilizing publicly available survey data of Bitcoin users, this analysis explores the structure of the Bitcoin community in terms of wealth accumulation, optimism about the future of Bitcoin, and themes that attract users to the cryptocurrency. Results indicate that age, time of initial use, geographic location, mining status, engaging online discourse, and political orientation are all relevant factors that help explain various aspects of Bitcoin wealth, optimism, and attraction	| 	
